Interface FieldObject

All Known Implementing Classes:

  • Method Details

    • canMove

      boolean canMove(Field.Direction dir)
      Determines if this object can move in given Field.Direction.
      Parameters:
      dir - Direction to move in.
      Returns:
      True if this object can move, false otherwise.

    • move

      boolean move(Field.Direction dir)
      Moves this object in given Field.Direction. Throws UnsupportedOperationException if object type is immovable.
      Parameters:
      dir - Direction to move in.
      Returns:
      True if successful, false otherwise.

    • getField

      Field getField()
      Returns a reference to Field, where this object is stored in.
      Returns:
      Reference to Field, where this object is stored in.

    • getLives

      int getLives()
      Returns number of lives of given object. For immortal object types returns 1.
      Returns:
      Number of lives.

    • loseLive

      void loseLive()
      Decrements number of lives by 1. Throws UnsupportedOperationException if object is immortal.

    • setLives

      void setLives(int lives)
      Sets object lives count. Throws UnsupportedOperationException if object is immortal.
      Parameters:
      lives - Number to set lives to.

    • setMaze

      void setMaze(Maze maze)
      Sets a reference to Maze.
      Parameters:
      maze - maze to set the reference to.

    • teleportTo

      void teleportTo(int row, int col)
      Teleports object to given location. Throws UnsupportedOperationException if object type is immovable.
      Parameters:
      row - Row index of destination.
      col - Column index of destination.
